    + 'The basin is the bittersweet landing site of Beagle 2, the British-built lander that separated from ESA\'s Mars Express orbiter on December 19, 2003. Contact was lost during the Christmas Day landing attempt, and Beagle 2 was declared lost in February 2004. Then, eleven years later, NASA\'s Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter spotted it sitting on the surface just 5 km from its target landing zone. High-resolution images revealed that it had landed successfully but only partially deployed its solar panels, which physically blocked the communications antenna. Beagle 2 made it to Mars — it just could not phone home.\n\n'
