    + 'The crater\'s interior tells a rich geological story. Its floor contains layered sedimentary deposits, wind-sculpted dune fields, and erosional features that suggest it once held standing water. The eastern rim intersects with several smaller craters, creating a complex overlapping topography that allows geologists to establish relative age relationships — a critical technique for building Mars\'s geological timescale. Dark sand dunes on the crater floor, fed by basaltic sediment, create striking visual contrast against the lighter-toned surrounding terrain.\n\n'
